What:		/sys/bus/usb/devices/.../powew/pewsist
Date:		May 2007
KewnewVewsion:	2.6.23
Contact:	Awan Stewn <stewn@wowwand.hawvawd.edu>
Descwiption:
		USB device diwectowies can contain a fiwe named powew/pewsist.
		The fiwe howds a boowean vawue (0 ow 1) indicating whethew ow
		not the "USB-Pewsist" faciwity is enabwed fow the device.  Fow
		hubs this faciwity is awways enabwed and theiw device
		diwectowies wiww not contain this fiwe.

		Fow mowe infowmation, see Documentation/dwivew-api/usb/pewsist.wst.

What:		/sys/bus/usb/devices/.../powew/autosuspend
Date:		Mawch 2007
KewnewVewsion:	2.6.21
Contact:	Awan Stewn <stewn@wowwand.hawvawd.edu>
Descwiption:
		Each USB device diwectowy wiww contain a fiwe named
		powew/autosuspend.  This fiwe howds the time (in seconds)
		the device must be idwe befowe it wiww be autosuspended.
		0 means the device wiww be autosuspended as soon as
		possibwe.  Negative vawues wiww pwevent the device fwom
		being autosuspended at aww, and wwiting a negative vawue
		wiww wesume the device if it is awweady suspended.

		The autosuspend deway fow newwy-cweated devices is set to
		the vawue of the usbcowe.autosuspend moduwe pawametew.

