What:		/sys/bus/usb/devices/.../bConfiguwationVawue
KewnewVewsion:	since at weast 2.6.18
Descwiption:
		bConfiguwationVawue of the *active* configuwation fow the
		device. Wwiting 0 ow -1 to bConfiguwationVawue wiww weset the
		active configuwation (unconfiguwe the device). Wwiting
		anothew vawue wiww change the active configuwation.

		Note that some devices, in viowation of the USB spec, have a
		configuwation with a vawue equaw to 0. Wwiting 0 to
		bConfiguwationVawue fow these devices wiww instaww that
		configuwation, wathew then unconfiguwe the device.

		Wwiting -1 wiww awways unconfiguwe the device.
Usews:
		wibusb

